This paper deals with natural language processing and neural networks, which are typically covered in the arXiv CS sub-categories of computational linguistics (cs.CL), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of neural units and their behavior, which could fall under the sub-category of neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper includes a case study on English to Mandarin Chinese translation, which could be relevant to computer vision (cs.CV) as well.
